finding.suggested_fix:
Move both useState calls to the top of OnboardingPage, before any conditional returns:

```tsx
export function OnboardingPage({ loading, hasOrgs }: { loading: boolean; hasOrgs: boolean }) {
  const [name, setName] = useState("");
  const [slug, setSlug] = useState("");

  if (loading) return <div>Loading...</div>;
  if (hasOrgs) return <Navigate to="/home" replace />;

  return <div>{name}{slug}</div>;
}
```

This satisfies React's Rules of Hooks: every hook is called unconditionally on every render, in the same order.

